This paper deals with the problem of developing optimal routing and caching policies in a hybrid network consisting of MANET nodes and cellular infrastructure. The focus is on minimizing overall content-access delay. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and systems and control (cs.SY).
